This tweet discusses Dolphin, an open-source document parsing framework developed by ByteDance that enables users to convert PDF files into clean, structured data formats. The tool appears to be designed for machine learning and data processing applications, allowing easy transformation of PDF documents into more accessible and machine-readable formats like Markdown, HTML, LaTeX, and JSON. By making the framework 100% open-source, ByteDance is providing developers and researchers with a flexible tool for document parsing and data extraction, which could be particularly useful for AI training, research, and information processing tasks.

This French-language blog post from Kompozite focuses on explaining the CO2 equivalent (CO2e), a critical unit of measurement for greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions. The article aims to help readers understand why this standardized metric is important for quantifying and comparing different types of greenhouse gases. CO2 equivalent allows for a unified approach to measuring the global warming potential of various gases by converting them to a common scale based on carbon dioxide's impact. This helps scientists, policymakers, and organizations track and communicate climate change impacts more effectively, as different greenhouse gases have varying levels of warming potential over different time periods.
